---
import Base from '../../../layouts/PlottedBase.astro';
import LifeExpectancyChart from '../../../components/LifeExpectancyChart.astro';
import { pieces } from '../../../data/plotted-pieces';

const piece = pieces.find((p) => p.slug === 'a-lengthening-life')!;
---

<Base title={`${piece.title} · Plotted`} description={piece.dek}>
  <article class="piece">
    <header class="piece-head" data-reveal>
      <p class="kicker">{piece.kicker}</p>
      <h1>{piece.title}</h1>
      <p class="standfirst measure">{piece.dek}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose measure" data-reveal>
      <p>
        Life expectancy is a strange, useful fiction. It asks: if the death
        rates of a single year held for a lifetime, how long would a newborn
        live? For almost all of history the answer barely moved: around three
        decades, held down not by old age but by the sheer number of children
        who never reached it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <LifeExpectancyChart />

    <div class="prose measure" data-reveal>
      <p>
        Then the line breaks upward. Not evenly, and not without cost. The 1918
        influenza pandemic wiped out a century of progress in a single year. But
        after 1950 something genuinely new happens: antibiotics, vaccines, clean
        water and oral rehydration reach almost everywhere at once, and the whole
        world rises together. A child born today can expect more than twice the
        life of one born in 1800.
      </p>
      <p>
        The averages hide the real drama. Toggle a country onto the chart and
        the unevenness appears: the United Kingdom started high and climbed
        steadily; South Korea began below the world average and, within two
        generations, overtook it. The gap between the luckiest and unluckiest
        places to be born has been both the great scandal and the great
        opportunity of the last century. COVID-19 aside, it has mostly been
        closing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <footer class="piece-foot measure" data-reveal>
      <hr class="rule" />
      <dl class="meta">
        <div><dt>Source</dt><dd><a href={piece.source.url}>{piece.source.name}</a></dd></div>
        <div><dt>License</dt><dd>{piece.source.license}</dd></div>
        <div><dt>Built with</dt><dd>Astro · D3 · hand-set type</dd></div>
      </dl>
      <p class="back"><a href="/plotted">← Back to the gallery</a></p>
    </footer>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .piece { width: var(--frame); margin: 0 auto; }
  .piece-head { padding: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-4); }
  .piece-head h1 { font-size: var(--step-5); margin: var(--space-2) 0 var(--space-3); max-width: 18ch; }
  .standfirst { font-size: var(--step-2); line-height: 1.35; color: var(--ink-soft); font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 400; }
  .prose { margin: var(--space-4) 0; }
  .prose p { font-size: var(--step-1); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 var(--space-3); }
  .prose p:first-child::first-letter {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3.4em;
    float: left;
    line-height: 0.8;
    padding: 0.08em 0.1em 0 0;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .piece-foot { margin-top: var(--space-5); }
  .meta { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--space-4); margin: 0; font-size: var(--step--1); }
  .meta dt { font-family: var(--font-mono); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--ink-faint); margin-bottom: 2px; }
  .meta dd { margin: 0; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .meta a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
  .meta a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .back { margin-top: var(--space-4); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--step--1); }
  .back a { color: var(--ink-soft); text-decoration: none; }
  .back a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
</style>
